com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class RejectMessageGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.RejectMessageGenerator

  • public final class RejectMessageGenerator
extends Object
    This class provides convenience methods for generating FIX version specific reject messages.

    When using this API, client code is responsible for providing enough information via the 'messageToReject' parameter in order to generate a valid reject message, or must add this information to the reject message before sending it. See Javadoc for each method below.

      • createFixVersionDependentBusinessMessageReject

        public static IFIXMessage createFixVersionDependentBusinessMessageReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                                                         ITagValues messageToReject,
                                                                         FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                                                         int rejectReasonCode,
                                                                         int tagToReject,
                                                                         String rejectReasonText,
                                                                         boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates a Reject [type '3'] or BusinessMessageReject (a.k.a. BMR) [type 'j'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided. For FIX.4.2 and above versions, a BusinessReject (a.k.a. BMR) [type 'j'] message is generated; for all the other versions below, a Reject [type '3'] is generated.

        If a negative rejectReasonCode is supplied then a 0(Other) reason will be set as the business reject reason code, and nothing will be set as a session reject reason code.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Session Reject:

        • RefSeqNum(FIX tag 45) is fetched from MsgSeqNum(FIX tag 34) of messageToReject.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Business Message Reject:

        • RefMsgType(FIX tag 372) is fetched from MsgType(FIX tag 35) of messageToReject.
        • BusinessRejectReason(FIX tag 380) is passed in as rejectReasonCode or set as 0(Other) if a negative value is supplied.
        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        messageToReject - A FIX message to be rejected.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        rejectReasonCode - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Optional. It will only be set if it is >= 0.
        tagToReject - A FIX tag that may need to be added to the reject in case of a specific problem with this tag (e.g. tag missing). It will only be set if a Reject [type '3'] is being generated and its value is > 0.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates FIX tag 58. If none provided then the human readable text corresponding to this reject reason code or/and tagToReject will be used to populate tag 58.
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        SessionRejectReason, BusinessMessageRejectReason

      • createFixVersionDependentBusinessMessageReject

        public static IFIXMessage createFixVersionDependentBusinessMessageReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                                                         ITagValues messageToReject,
                                                                         FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                                                         String rejectReasonText,
                                                                         boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates a Reject [type '3'] or BusinessMessageReject (a.k.a. BMR) [type 'j'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided. For FIX.4.2 and above versions, a BusinessReject (a.k.a. BMR) [type 'j'] message is generated; for all the other versions below, a Reject [type '3'] is generated.

        Can be used in cases when the reject reason is unknown. Nothing will be set in a Reject and 0(Other) will be set in a BusinessMessageReject as the reject reason code.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Session Reject:

        • RefSeqNum(FIX tag 45) is fetched from MsgSeqNum(FIX tag 34) of messageToReject.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Business Message Reject:

        • RefMsgType(FIX tag 372) is fetched from MsgType(FIX tag 35) of messageToReject.
        • BusinessRejectReason(FIX tag 380) will be set to 0(Other).
        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        messageToReject - A FIX message to be rejected.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates FIX tag 58.
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        SessionRejectReason, BusinessMessageRejectReason

      • createSessionReject

        public static IFIXMessage createSessionReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                              ITagValues messageToReject,
                                              FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                              int sessionRejectReasonCode,
                                              int tagToReject,
                                              String rejectReasonText,
                                              boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates a Reject [type '3'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Session Reject:

        • RefSeqNum(FIX tag 45) is fetched from MsgSeqNum(FIX tag 34) of messageToReject.
        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        messageToReject - A FIX message to be rejected.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        sessionRejectReasonCode - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Value populates tag 373. It will only be set if it is >= 0.
        tagToReject - A FIX tag that may need to be added to the reject in case of specific problem with this tag (e.g. tag missing). It will only be set if it is > 0.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; For FIX version >= 4.2 populates the Text(FIX tag 58) otherwise from this text and sessionRejectReasonCode/tagToReject (if provided) will be compounded a human-readable message.
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        SessionRejectReason

        public static IFIXMessage createSessionReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,

                                              int refSeqNum,

        Generates a Reject [type '3'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided using the information provided.

      • createOrderReject

        public static IFIXMessage createOrderReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                            ITagValues orderRequest,
                                            FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                            String execID,
                                            String orderID,
                                            Integer ordRejReasonCode,
                                            String rejectReasonText,
                                            boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates a Execution Report [type '8'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Order Reject:

        OrderID(FIX tag 37) is fetched from OrderID(FIX tag 37) of orderRequest. If orderRequest does not contain tag 37, the provided orderID parameter will be used instead.

        Instrument information block depends on FIX version and is fetched from orderRequest.

        Side(FIX tag 54) and all Quantity tags are populated from the corresponding tags of orderRequest.

        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        orderRequest - A FIX message to be rejected.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        execID - An ExecID which will be used to construct this Execution Report. Will not be set if null. Then it is the application's responsibility to set this tag before sending the reject.
        orderID - An OrderID which will be used to construct this Execution Report if it not available from orderRequest. If orderRequest does not contain an OrderId and this parameter is null it is the application's responsibility to set this tag before sending the reject.
        ordRejReasonCode - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Populates FIX tag 103. Will not be set if null.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates FIX tag 58
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        OrderRejectReason

      • createOrderCancelReject

        public static IFIXMessage createOrderCancelReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                                  ITagValues orderCancelReplaceRequest,
                                                  ITagValues originalOrder,
                                                  String orderID,
                                                  FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                                  Integer cxlRejectReason,
                                                  String rejectReasonText,
                                                  boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates an Order Cancel Reject [type '9'] message depending upon the FIX protocol version provided which is used for rejecting both cancel request or cancel/replace request.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Order Cancel Reject:

        OrderID(FIX tag 37) is fetched from OrderID(FIX tag 37) of originalOrder (or from orderCancelReplaceRequest if not available in originalOrder). Otherwise the provided orderID parameter is used.

        ClOrdID(FIX tag 11) is fetched from OrderID(FIX tag 11) of orderCancelReplaceRequest.

        If FIXVersion >= 4.1 then OrigClOrdID(FIX tag 41) is fetched from ClOrdID(FIX tag 41) of orderCancelReplaceRequest.

        If FIXVersion >= 4.2 then CxlRejResponse(FIX tag 434) is fetched from MsgType(FIX tag 35) of orderCancelReplaceRequest (identifies is this is a reject for a Cancel or for Cancel/Replace request).

        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        orderCancelReplaceRequest - A cancel or cancel/replace to generate reject for.
        originalOrder - An original order for which cancel or cancel/replace request are rejected.
        orderID - An OrderID which will be used to construct this Execution Report if it is not available from originalOrder and orderCancelReplaceRequest. If CxlRejReason="Unknown order" OrderID will be set to "NONE". OrderID will not be set if it isn't part of originalOrder/orderCancelReplaceRequest and this parameter is null. Then it is the application's responsibility to provide it before sending the reject.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        cxlRejectReason - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Populates FIX tag 102. Will not be set if null is supplied.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates FIX tag 58
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        OrderCancelRejectReason

        Parameters:

        orderCancelReplaceRequest - A cancel or cancel/replace to generate reject for.
        originalOrder - An original order for which cancel or cancel/replace request are rejected.
        orderID - An OrderID which will be used to construct this Execution Report if it is not available from originalOrder and orderCancelReplaceRequest. If CxlRejReason="Unknown order" OrderID will be set to "NONE". OrderID will not be set if it isn't part of originalOrder/orderCancelReplaceRequest and this parameter is null. Then it is the application's responsibility to provide it before sending the reject.
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        cxlRejectReason - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Populates FIX tag 102. Will not be set if null is supplied.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates FIX tag 58
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.

      • createFixVersionDependentQuoteRequestReject

        public static IFIXMessage createFixVersionDependentQuoteRequestReject(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                                                      ITagValues quoteRequestMessage,
                                                                      FIXVersion fixVersion,
                                                                      int rejectReasonCode,
                                                                      String rejectReasonText,
                                                                      boolean swapCompIds)

        Generates a SessionReject type['3'] or QuoteAcknowledgement [Type 'b'] or QuoteRequestReject [type 'AG'] message for FIX protocol versions 4.1 and earlier or 4.2 or 4.3 and later respectively.
        The Quote Request Reject message is used to reject Quote Request messages for all quoting models.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid Quote Request Reject:

        For FIX version <= 4.1 using SessionReject

        RefSeqNum(FIX tag 45) is fetched from MsgSeqNum(FIX tag 34) of messageToReject.

        For FIX version = 4.2 using QuoteAcknowledgement

        QuoteReqID(FIX tag 131) is fetched from QuoteReqID(FIX tag 131) of quoteRequestMessage.

        For FIX version >= 4.3 using QuoteRequestReject

        QuoteReqID(FIX tag 131) is fetched from QuoteReqID(FIX tag 131) of quoteRequestMessage.

        Instrument information block depends on FIX version and is fetched from orderRequest.

        QuoteRequestRejectReason(FIX tag 658)

        A valid reject reason code must be provided as given value will be used as is.
        Refer to OrderRejectReason or QuoteRequestRejectReason for all possible values for the rejectReasonCode.

        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        quoteRequestMessage - The Quote Request message to reject
        fixVersion - A FIX version
        rejectReasonCode - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Value populates either of FIX tag 658 or 300 or 373 or 380 depending upon the FIX protocol version.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates the Text (FIX tag 58)
        swapCompIds - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        An IFIXMessage representing the FIX reject.
        See Also:
        for all possible values of quoteRejectReasonCode., for all possible values of quoteRejectReasonCode.

      • createDontKnowTrade

        public static IFIXMessage createDontKnowTrade(IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                                              ITagValues executionReportMessage,
                                              char dkReasonCode,
                                              String rejectReasonText,
                                              boolean swapCompIDs)

        Generates a Don't Know Trade (a.k.a. DK) [type 'Q'] message.

        Mandatory FIX tags for creating a valid DontKnowTrade:

        OrderID(FIX tag 37) is fetched from OrderID(FIX tag 37) of executionReportMessage.

        ExecID(FIX tag 17) is fetched from ExecID(FIX tag 17) of executionReportMessage.

        Instrument information block depends on FIX version and is fetched from orderRequest.

        Side(FIX tag 54) is fetched from Side(FIX tag 54) of executionReportMessage.

        DKReason(FIX tag 127) is provided in the dkReasonCode.

        A valid reject reason code must be provided as given value will be used as is.
        Refer to DontKnowTradeReason for all possible values for the dkReasonCode.

        Parameters:
        factory - A factory to create the FIX message.
        executionReportMessage - The message to generate dontKnowTrade for.
        dkReasonCode - A valid reason code to be added to the reject message. Value populates tag 127. If reason unknown then 'Z'(Other) should be provided as a reject reason code.
        rejectReasonText - A text representing a problem description; populates tag 58. If null then the text corresponding to this dkReasonCode will be used.
        swapCompIDs - whether compids in the resulting reject message should be swapped relative to the message being rejected
        Returns:
        IFIXMessage The DontKnowTrade message.
        See Also:
        for all possible values of dkReasonCode.
